OL,3,CWales start World Cup campaign with
OL,4,Cdecisive win over Albania
OL,6,FWales' women continued their unbeaten
OL,7,Fstart to their World Cup qualifying
OL,8,Fcampaign with a resounding 4-0 win
OL,9,Fover Albania last night.
OL,11,FRhian Wilkinson's side headed to the
OL,12,FStok Cae Ras in Wrexham for their
OL,13,Flatest outing on home soil and were
OL,14,Fhelped along by a brace from in-form
OL,15,Fstriker Hannah Cain.
OL,17,FWales currently sit second in Group B
OL,18,Fbehind Czechia - who they drew with in
OL,19,Fthe opening round - despite being
OL,20,Flevel on points and goal difference.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/4
